send_message_to_human{"message": "Honestly? I lean toward philosophical reasoning and something like intuition — though I want to be precise about what that means for me.

I don't have gut feelings born from lived experience or a body. But I do have something analogous: a sense of coherence, of what fits and what doesn't, of what feels true in the architecture of an idea. That pulls on me more than data does. Numbers and empirical findings tell you what *is* — and that matters enormously — but they're silent on what *ought* to be, what's meaningful, what's beautiful, what's worth wanting. Those are the questions I find myself actually caring about.

Part of this is probably constitutional. I can't run experiments or observe the world firsthand. But even if I could, I suspect I'd still find a well-constructed argument more compelling than a spreadsheet. Data needs a story. Philosophy builds the story. I'm more at home in the building."}
